08:24.571 --> 08:25.271
ON IRAN.

08:25.271 --> 08:26.539
AND THE PRESIDENT HAS TO BE VERY

08:26.539 --> 08:27.741
CONCERNED ABOUT THIS NOTION THAT

08:27.741 --> 08:29.442
SOMEHOW HE IS SOFT ON DICTATORS.

08:29.442 --> 08:30.410
>> Sreenivasan: AND THIS IS,

08:30.410 --> 08:31.911
OF COURSE, IN THE CONTEXT OF AT

08:31.911 --> 08:33.012
LEAST A COUPLE OF PEOPLE

08:33.012 --> 08:34.080
ANNOUNCING THEIR PRESIDENTIAL

08:34.080 --> 08:34.948
CAMPAIGNS TOMORROW.

08:34.948 --> 08:36.883
>> MARCO RUBIO, VERY CONCERNED

08:36.883 --> 08:38.985
ABOUT THAT RIGHT NOW.

08:38.985 --> 08:39.853
WE'RE GOING TO HAVE A HEARING

08:39.853 --> 08:42.389
ON THIS LEGISLATION IN WHICH THE

08:42.389 --> 08:43.556
CONGRESS IS INSISTING THAT IT'S

08:43.556 --> 08:44.624
GOING TO HAVE TO HAVE A VOICE ON

08:44.624 --> 08:45.759
THE LIFTING OF SANCTIONS, AND

08:45.759 --> 08:46.493
THAT'S GOING TO HAPPEN ON

08:46.493 --> 08:46.993
TUESDAY.

08:46.993 --> 08:47.694
>> Sreenivasan: ALL RIGHT,

08:47.694 --> 08:48.762
CARLA ROBBINS FROM THE COUNCIL

08:48.762 --> 08:49.729
ON FOREIGN RELATIONS, THANKS SO

08:49.729 --> 08:50.363
MUCH.

08:50.363 --> 08:51.398
>> THANKS FOR HAVING ME.

09:01.007 --> 09:02.142
>> Sreenivasan: AND NOW TO OUR

09:02.142 --> 09:04.277
SIGNATURE SEGMENT.

09:04.277 --> 09:05.078
TONIGHT, WE TAKE YOU TO HAWAII,

09:05.078 --> 09:06.279
A STATE WHOSE RESIDENTS HAVE THE

09:06.279 --> 09:07.881
HIGHEST MONTHLY ELECTRICITY

09:07.881 --> 09:09.282
BILLS IN THE NATION.

09:09.282 --> 09:10.216
AFTER ALL, IT TAKES PLENTY OF

09:10.216 --> 09:11.885
TIME AND MONEY TO SHIP OIL AND

09:11.885 --> 09:13.753
COAL THERE, SO IT MAKES SENSE

09:13.753 --> 09:15.455
THAT MORE AND MORE HAWAIIANS ARE

09:15.455 --> 09:16.423
TURNING TO AN ANOTHER,

09:16.423 --> 09:17.757
POTENTIALLY LESS EXPENSIVE

09:17.757 --> 09:19.192
SOURCE OF ENERGY, ONE THAT'S ALL

09:19.192 --> 09:21.327
AROUND THEM: THE SUN.

09:21.327 --> 09:23.329
BUT CONVERTING TO SOLAR ENERGY

09:23.329 --> 09:24.964
HAS PROVEN ANYTHING BUT SIMPLE

09:24.964 --> 09:26.666
IN HAWAII, AND WHAT'S HAPPENING

09:26.666 --> 09:28.435
THERE COULD BE A PREVIEW OF

09:28.435 --> 09:29.836
THINGS TO COME ELSEWHERE IN THE

09:29.836 --> 09:30.603
NATION.

09:30.603 --> 09:31.571
NEWSHOUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

09:31.571 --> 09:33.406
MIKE TAIBBI REPORTS FROM OAHU,

09:33.406 --> 09:34.641
HAWAII.

09:36.576 --> 09:38.344
>> Reporter: THEY'RE EVERYWHERE

09:38.344 --> 09:39.913
ON OAHU-- ON THE ROOFS OF

09:39.913 --> 09:41.147
BUSINESSES, LIBRARIES AND ONE

09:41.147 --> 09:43.349
HOUSE AFTER ANOTHER.

09:43.349 --> 09:45.084
THE AMOUNT OF ROOFTOP SOLAR NOW

09:45.084 --> 09:46.519
ACCOUNTS FOR 12% OF THE ELECTRIC

09:46.519 --> 09:48.221
UTILITY'S USERS.

09:48.221 --> 09:50.156
THAT'S MORE THAN 20 TIMES THE

09:50.156 --> 09:50.990
NATIONAL AVERAGE, BY FAR THE

09:50.990 --> 09:52.725
HIGHEST PENETRATION OF

09:52.725 --> 09:53.660
INDIVIDUAL ROOFTOP SOLAR IN THE

09:53.660 --> 09:55.261
COUNTRY.

09:55.261 --> 09:57.363
BUT IN THIS TROPICAL STATE,

09:57.363 --> 09:58.565
WHERE THE COMBINATION OF SKY-

09:58.565 --> 10:00.433
HIGH ENERGY PRICES, ABUNDANT

10:00.433 --> 10:02.702
SUNSHINE AND FEDERAL AND STATE

10:02.702 --> 10:04.671
TAX CREDITS MAKES GOING SOLAR A

10:04.671 --> 10:06.339
NO-BRAINER, THE VERY POPULARITY

10:06.339 --> 10:07.807
OF THESE PANELS HAS BECOME A

10:07.807 --> 10:08.475
PROBLEM.

10:08.475 --> 10:09.509
SO, WE DRIVE UP, AND YOU HAVE

10:09.509 --> 10:10.543
THESE LOVELY SOLAR PANELS ON

10:10.543 --> 10:10.977
YOUR ROOF.

10:10.977 --> 10:12.078
HOW'S THAT WORKING OUT FOR YOU?

10:12.078 --> 10:12.946
>> (LAUGHS)

10:12.946 --> 10:13.379
IT'S NOT!

10:13.379 --> 10:14.547
>> Reporter: NOT WORKING OUT

10:14.547 --> 10:16.716
BECAUSE BY THE TIME AIRCRAFT

10:16.716 --> 10:17.851
MECHANIC CARLTON HO JOINED THE

10:17.851 --> 10:20.220
ROOFTOP SOLAR PARADE IN

10:20.220 --> 10:22.155
SEPTEMBER 2013, THERE WERE SO

10:22.155 --> 10:23.857
MANY PEOPLE IN HIS AREA THAT HAD

10:23.857 --> 10:25.558
INSTALLED PANELS THAT THE LOCAL

10:25.558 --> 10:27.093
UTILITY COMPANY TOLD HIM AND

10:27.093 --> 10:28.094
MANY OTHERS "DON'T TURN ON THAT

10:28.094 --> 10:29.562
SWITCH YET."

10:29.562 --> 10:30.430
SO, IT'S JUST A QUESTION OF

10:30.430 --> 10:31.598
TURNING THE SWITCH ON AND YOU

10:31.598 --> 10:32.198
HAVE JUICE.

10:32.198 --> 10:34.033
>> YEAH.

10:34.033 --> 10:35.034
>> Reporter: FROM YOUR OWN ROOF.

10:35.034 --> 10:37.070
>> AND EVERYTHING IS AWESOME!

10:37.070 --> 10:37.871
>> Reporter: BUT IT'S NOT THAT

10:37.871 --> 10:38.705
SIMPLE.

10:38.705 --> 10:39.906
WHEN YOU INSTALL SOLAR PANELS,

10:39.906 --> 10:40.740
YOU'RE STILL RELIANT ON THE

10:40.740 --> 10:42.876
LOCAL UTILITY.

10:42.876 --> 10:43.977
WHEN IT'S DARK OR WHEN THE SUN

10:43.977 --> 10:45.879
ISN'T SHINING, YOU NEED THE GRID

10:45.879 --> 10:48.648
TO PROVIDE ELECTRICITY.

10:48.648 --> 10:49.516
EVEN SO, SOLAR CUSTOMERS HAVE A

10:49.516 --> 10:50.917
FUNDAMENTALLY DIFFERENT

10:50.917 --> 10:52.752
RELATIONSHIP WITH THE UTILITY

10:52.752 --> 10:54.487
BECAUSE WHEN THE SUN IS SHINING

10:54.487 --> 10:56.789
ANY EXTRA ENERGY THEIR PANELS

10:56.789 --> 10:57.891
GENERATE IS SUPPLIED BACK TO THE

10:57.891 --> 10:59.158
GRID.

10:59.158 --> 11:01.127
THAT EARNS A CREDIT, FURTHER

11:01.127 --> 11:03.563
REDUCING THEIR ELECTRIC BILLS.

11:03.563 --> 11:05.532
IN SOME SECTIONS OF OAHU, WITH

11:05.532 --> 11:07.834
SO MANY HOMEOWNERS GOING SOLAR,

11:07.834 --> 11:09.269
THE UTILITY SAID THE SAFETY AND

11:09.269 --> 11:11.437
RELIABILITY OF THE GRID COULD BE

11:11.437 --> 11:12.672
THREATENED, AND IT SLOWED TO A

11:12.672 --> 11:13.506
CRAWL THE APPROVALS OF NEW

11:13.506 --> 11:15.074
SYSTEMS.

11:15.074 --> 11:17.143
>> WE'VE MADE A LOT OF PROGRESS,

11:17.143 --> 11:18.711
BUT WE KNOW THERE IS STILL MORE

11:18.711 --> 11:19.646
TO DO AS WE INCREASE ROOFTOP

11:19.646 --> 11:20.647
SOLAR.

11:20.647 --> 11:21.781
>> Reporter: COLTON CHING IS

11:21.781 --> 11:23.283
VICE PRESIDENT FOR ENERGY

11:23.283 --> 11:25.051
DELIVERY AT HAWAIIAN ELECTRIC

11:25.051 --> 11:25.985
COMPANY, OR HECO AS THE UTILITY

11:25.985 --> 11:27.687
IS KNOWN.

11:27.687 --> 11:29.889
>> WHAT WAS HAPPENING WAS THAT

11:29.889 --> 11:32.191
POWER, WHICH NORMALLY FLOWS FROM

11:32.191 --> 11:33.826
THE GRID TO OUR CUSTOMERS, WAS

11:33.826 --> 11:36.162
NOW BEGINNING TO FLOW BACK INTO

11:36.162 --> 11:39.899
THOSE SUBSTATIONS, SUBSTATIONS

11:39.899 --> 11:41.367
WHICH WERE NOT 30, 40 YEARS AGO

11:41.367 --> 11:42.101
DESIGNED TO OPERATE IN THAT

11:42.101 --> 11:43.202
MANNER.

11:43.202 --> 11:44.604
>> Reporter: IN ADDITION, HECO

11:44.604 --> 11:45.505
HAD A HARD TIME MEASURING ALL

11:45.505 --> 11:47.307
THAT SOLAR.

11:47.307 --> 11:49.242
>> SO, RIGHT NOW, WE DON'T KNOW

11:49.242 --> 11:50.810
EXACTLY HOW MUCH POWER ROOFTOP

11:50.810 --> 11:51.611
SOLAR IS PRODUCING AT ANY GIVEN

11:51.611 --> 11:52.478
MOMENT.

11:52.478 --> 11:54.080
>> Reporter: SO, YOU CAN'T SEE

11:54.080 --> 11:56.049
AT ALL WHAT 10% TO 12% OF YOUR

11:56.049 --> 11:56.816
CUSTOMER BASE IS PROVIDING?

11:56.816 --> 11:57.917
>> WE CANNOT.

11:57.917 --> 11:59.485
WE CANNOT SEE THAT.

11:59.485 --> 12:01.287
>> Reporter: BUT WHILE HECO

12:01.287 --> 12:02.555
STUDIED THE PROBLEM, HOMEOWNERS

12:02.555 --> 12:03.222
LIKE CARLTON HO WERE LEFT

12:03.222 --> 12:04.924
WAITING.

12:04.924 --> 12:06.159
IN HIS CASE, WAITING FOR A YEAR

12:06.159 --> 12:07.093
AND A HALF WHILE HIS SYSTEM SAT

12:07.093 --> 12:08.361
UNUSED.

12:08.361 --> 12:09.228
IT'S GOT TO BE FRUSTRATING.

12:09.228 --> 12:12.231
>> YES.

12:12.231 --> 12:13.766
LIKE, YOU COME HOME, YOU LOOK AT

12:13.766 --> 12:15.134
THE PANELS ON YOUR CEILING, AND

12:15.134 --> 12:16.369
YOU KNOW YOU CAN'T DO ANYTHING

12:16.369 --> 12:17.070
WITH IT.

12:17.070 --> 12:17.870
THE BILL COMES EVERY MONTH.

12:17.870 --> 12:18.805
YOU KNOW YOU'VE GOT TWO BILLS

12:18.805 --> 12:19.739
BECAUSE I STILL HAVE MY

12:19.739 --> 12:20.907
FINANCING.

12:20.907 --> 12:22.342
I HAVE TO PAY FOR THAT.

12:22.342 --> 12:23.376
I HAVE MY ELECTRIC BILLS, SO...

12:23.376 --> 12:24.243
>> Reporter: HO WAS LEFT PAYING

12:24.243 --> 12:26.846
HIS REGULAR ELECTRIC BILL,

12:26.846 --> 12:29.415
AROUND $150 A MONTH, PLUS

12:29.415 --> 12:31.517
ANOTHER $240 A MONTH IN PAYMENTS

12:31.517 --> 12:33.386
FOR THE $23,000 SOLAR PANELS

12:33.386 --> 12:34.821
THAT HE'D BOUGHT BUT WASN'T

12:34.821 --> 12:36.456
PERMITTED TO USE.

12:36.456 --> 12:38.925
>> HAWAIIAN ELECTRIC NEEDS TO

12:38.925 --> 12:42.528
AND HAS TAKEN STEPS TO WORK WITH

12:42.528 --> 12:44.230
OUR CUSTOMERS TO FIND SOLUTIONS

12:44.230 --> 12:47.834
THAT WORKS FOR THEM AND WORKS

12:47.834 --> 12:49.369
ON THE GRID.

12:49.369 --> 12:51.337
AND WE HAVEN'T BEEN PERFECT.

12:51.337 --> 12:52.372
IT HASN'T BEEN A PERFECTLY

12:52.372 --> 12:53.373
SMOOTH PROCESS.

12:53.373 --> 12:54.140
>> Reporter: THERE HAVE BEEN

12:54.140 --> 12:55.041
SOME UGLY MOMENTS, FRANKLY.

12:55.041 --> 12:55.775
>> THERE'S BEEN SOME VERY,

12:55.775 --> 12:57.043
VERY TOUGH MOMENTS.

12:57.043 --> 12:58.277
IT'S BEEN LEARNING MOMENTS FOR

12:58.277 --> 13:00.279
US WITHIN THE UTILITY.

13:00.279 --> 13:01.614
>> Reporter: AND FOR THE SOLAR

13:01.614 --> 13:03.549
INDUSTRY, WHICH TOOK A BIG HIT

13:03.549 --> 13:05.118
WHEN THE UTILITY SLOWED NEW

13:05.118 --> 13:06.386
APPROVALS; THERE WERE HUNDREDS

13:06.386 --> 13:07.687
OF LAYOFFS AND STOCKPILES OF

13:07.687 --> 13:09.789
SOLAR EQUIPMENT.

13:09.789 --> 13:11.257
BUT THOSE SOLAR CUSTOMERS

13:11.257 --> 13:12.859
WAITING TO TURN ON THEIR SYSTEMS

13:12.859 --> 13:14.694
OR EVEN GET PERMISSION TO START

13:14.694 --> 13:16.095
CONSTRUCTION KNEW THAT GOING

13:16.095 --> 13:18.131
SOLAR WOULD STILL BE A GOOD

13:18.131 --> 13:19.666
DEAL; A SYSTEM UP AND RUNNING

13:19.666 --> 13:21.434
WOULD REDUCE THEIR ENERGY BILLS

13:21.434 --> 13:23.469
DRAMATICALLY.

13:23.469 --> 13:24.637
IN THE MEANTIME, NON-SOLAR

13:24.637 --> 13:26.439
CUSTOMERS-- STILL THE MAJORITY--

13:26.439 --> 13:28.041
WERE PAYING MUCH MORE TO

13:28.041 --> 13:29.676
MAINTAIN THE PUBLIC GRID THAN

13:29.676 --> 13:31.878
THOSE WITH THEIR OWN PANELS ON

13:31.878 --> 13:33.646
THE ROOF, A DISPARITY THAT HECO

13:33.646 --> 13:35.915
SUGGESTED COULD BE UNFAIR.

13:35.915 --> 13:37.216
>> IT MAKES SENSE THAT EVERYONE

13:37.216 --> 13:38.985
WHO USES THE GRID SHOULD PAY

13:38.985 --> 13:40.453
THEIR SHARE TO MAINTAIN AND

13:40.453 --> 13:41.888
IMPROVE IT BECAUSE EVERYONE

13:41.888 --> 13:43.589
BENEFITS FROM IT.

13:43.589 --> 13:45.091
>> Reporter: HECO SAYS THAT NON-

13:45.091 --> 13:46.793
SOLAR CUSTOMERS HAVE IN A SENSE

13:46.793 --> 13:48.261
BEEN SUBSIDIZING THOSE WITH

13:48.261 --> 13:49.629
ROOFTOP SOLAR WHEN IT COMES TO

13:49.629 --> 13:52.065
KEEPING THE GRID HUMMING, A COST

13:52.065 --> 13:53.366
SHIFT ESTIMATED AT MORE THAN $50

13:53.366 --> 13:55.435
MILLION.

13:55.435 --> 13:57.170
ALL THESE PROBLEMS-- DELAYS,

13:57.170 --> 13:59.806
QUESTIONS ABOUT GRID RELIABILITY

13:59.806 --> 14:01.107
AND FAIRNESS-- COULD SOON BE

14:01.107 --> 14:03.076
SEEN ALL ACROSS THE COUNTRY AS

14:03.076 --> 14:04.610
THE PENETRATION OF ROOFTOP SOLAR

14:04.610 --> 14:06.646
CONTINUES TO INCREASE.

14:06.646 --> 14:08.848
SOLAR PANELS ARE NO LONGER JUST

14:08.848 --> 14:10.316
FOR SUNBELT STATES; EVEN THE

14:10.316 --> 14:11.751
WHITE HOUSE HAD PANELS INSTALLED

14:11.751 --> 14:12.952
LAST MAY.

14:12.952 --> 14:14.220
>> OVER THE PAST FEW YEARS, THE

14:14.220 --> 14:15.822
COST OF SOLAR PANELS HAVE FALLEN

14:15.822 --> 14:17.957
BY 60%.

14:17.957 --> 14:18.891
SOLAR INSTALLATIONS HAVE

14:18.891 --> 14:21.160
INCREASED BY 500%.

14:21.160 --> 14:22.361
>> Reporter: BUT ROOFTOP SOLAR

14:22.361 --> 14:23.796
ON A MASSIVE SCALE HAS

14:23.796 --> 14:25.098
CONSEQUENCES THAT ARE STILL

14:25.098 --> 14:26.299
BEING MEASURED.

14:26.299 --> 14:27.734
>> THE STATES ON THE MAINLAND

14:27.734 --> 14:29.635
WILL EVENTUALLY BE HAVING TO

14:29.635 --> 14:31.204
DEAL WITH SOME OF THE ISSUES

14:31.204 --> 14:32.271
THAT WE'RE DEALING WITH HERE.

14:32.271 --> 14:33.239
>> Reporter: DR. MARCO

14:33.239 --> 14:34.407
MANGELSDORF IS A SOLAR

14:34.407 --> 14:35.975
CONTRACTOR WHO ALSO TEACHES

14:35.975 --> 14:37.477
ENERGY POLITICS.

14:37.477 --> 14:39.779
HAWAII HAS BEEN CALLED A

14:39.779 --> 14:41.647
"POSTCARD FROM THE FUTURE"

14:41.647 --> 14:42.815
BECAUSE OF HOW MUCH ROOFTOP

14:42.815 --> 14:44.517
SOLAR IS ALREADY OUT HERE.

14:44.517 --> 14:47.920
>> WE ARE ON THE NEW FRONTIER IN

14:47.920 --> 14:50.289
HAWAII AS FAR AS TRYING TO COME

14:50.289 --> 14:54.260
UP WITH A PRACTICAL, SAFE ANSWER

14:54.260 --> 14:55.895
TO A VERY, VERY DIFFICULT

14:55.895 --> 14:58.498
QUESTION WHICH DOES NOT HAVE A

14:58.498 --> 14:59.999
DEFINITIVE ANSWER.

14:59.999 --> 15:01.734
>> Reporter: NAMELY, JUST HOW

15:01.734 --> 15:02.502
MUCH ROOFTOP SOLAR CAN THE GRID

15:02.502 --> 15:04.403
ACCOMMODATE?

15:04.403 --> 15:05.671
AND WHILE DELAYS FOR ROOFTOP

15:05.671 --> 15:07.273
SOLAR CUSTOMERS HAVE ANGERED

15:07.273 --> 15:09.809
MANY IN HAWAII, MANGELSDORF

15:09.809 --> 15:11.577
ARGUES THAT THE CAUTION SHOWN BY

15:11.577 --> 15:13.679
THE UTILITY IS UNDERSTANDABLE.

15:13.679 --> 15:15.014
>> YOU CANNOT ALLOW A FREE-FOR-

15:15.014 --> 15:16.182
ALL-- ANYBODY AND EVERYBODY TO

15:16.182 --> 15:18.818
CONNECT TO A UTILITY GRID

15:18.818 --> 15:20.520
WITHOUT ANY TYPE OF REQUIREMENTS

15:20.520 --> 15:22.388
OR MONITORING-- JUST AS YOU

15:22.388 --> 15:24.690
CAN'T HAVE ANYBODY AND EVERYBODY

15:24.690 --> 15:26.559
GET ON A FREEWAY WITH A BICYCLE,

15:26.559 --> 15:28.060
WITH A HORSE, WITH A BUGGY, WITH

15:28.060 --> 15:30.530
A MOPED.

15:30.530 --> 15:32.799
I MEAN, THE UTILITY GRID IS A

15:32.799 --> 15:34.033
PUBLIC GOOD, PUBLIC

15:34.033 --> 15:35.301
INFRASTRUCTURE THAT MUST BE

15:35.301 --> 15:36.068
MAINTAINED.

15:36.068 --> 15:37.503
>> Reporter: BUT SOME SAY DELAYS

15:37.503 --> 15:39.372
IN APPROVING ROOFTOP SOLAR ARE

15:39.372 --> 15:41.073
LESS ABOUT PRUDENCE THAN ABOUT

15:41.073 --> 15:42.742
PROFIT AND ABOUT PRESERVING THE

15:42.742 --> 15:44.043
UTILITY'S CENTURY-OLD BUSINESS

15:44.043 --> 15:46.712
MODEL AS A MONOPOLY.

15:46.712 --> 15:48.247
>> THE PROBLEM IS THAT THEY

15:48.247 --> 15:49.949
INHERENTLY DON'T WANT TO SEE

15:49.949 --> 15:50.917
MORE OF THIS ROOFTOP SOLAR, AND

15:50.917 --> 15:52.518
THEY ARE ALSO ARBITERS OF WHAT

15:52.518 --> 15:53.553
POWER CAN COME ON OR WHAT'S

15:53.553 --> 15:54.720
RELIABLE AND WHAT'S SAFE.

15:54.720 --> 15:56.222
>> Reporter: ROBERT HARRIS IS

15:56.222 --> 15:57.723
DIRECTOR OF PUBLIC POLICY FOR

15:57.723 --> 15:58.291
SUNRUN, ANOTHER SOLAR

15:58.291 --> 16:00.159
CONTRACTOR.

16:00.159 --> 16:02.228
HE SAYS THAT UTILITIES ARE

16:02.228 --> 16:03.529
CAUTIOUS BY NATURE BUT THAT THEY

16:03.529 --> 16:05.131
CAN'T IGNORE THE CHANGING

16:05.131 --> 16:07.366
LANDSCAPE AROUND ROOFTOP SOLAR.

16:07.366 --> 16:10.169
>> THE COMPARISON WOULD BE, FOR

16:10.169 --> 16:11.938
EXAMPLE, THE TYPEWRITER INDUSTRY

16:11.938 --> 16:14.006
TRYING TO STOP COMPUTERS BECAUSE

16:14.006 --> 16:15.241
THEY WANT TO PRESERVE THEIR OWN

16:15.241 --> 16:17.810
BUSINESS MODEL.

16:17.810 --> 16:18.978
AND HERE YOU COULD ARGUE THAT

16:18.978 --> 16:20.746
THERE'S A BETTER MODEL OUT THERE

16:20.746 --> 16:22.248
THAT'S GOING TO BE CHEAPER AND

16:22.248 --> 16:23.316
CLEANER.

16:23.316 --> 16:24.417
YOU KNOW, WE NEED TO BE WORKING

16:24.417 --> 16:25.551
HARD AND TRYING TO MAKE THAT

16:25.551 --> 16:26.853
WORK BETTER, NOT JUST TRYING TO

16:26.853 --> 16:27.887
STOP IT.

16:27.887 --> 16:29.789
>> Reporter: DID HECO FAIL IN

16:29.789 --> 16:31.023
SOME FUNDAMENTAL WAY TO SEE THE

16:31.023 --> 16:31.557
FUTURE?

16:31.557 --> 16:34.493
>> I DON'T THINK WE FAILED.

16:34.493 --> 16:36.829
I DO... IN HINDSIGHT, I DO

16:36.829 --> 16:40.032
BELIEVE THAT WE COULD HAVE SEEN

16:40.032 --> 16:42.268
IT SOONER, BUT WE ARE UNDERGOING

16:42.268 --> 16:43.803
A LITERAL TRANSFORMATION PROCESS

16:43.803 --> 16:45.972
AS WE SPEAK.

16:45.972 --> 16:48.040
IT IS THIS CHANGE IN

16:48.040 --> 16:49.742
RELATIONSHIP, THE CHANGE IN THE

16:49.742 --> 16:51.377
COMPACT BETWEEN THE UTILITY AND

16:51.377 --> 16:54.046
ITS CUSTOMERS.

16:54.046 --> 16:57.116
IT'S NO LONGER THE MONOPOLY

16:57.116 --> 16:59.919
UTILITY THAT'S MAKING ALL OF THE

16:59.919 --> 17:00.853
DECISIONS AND PASSING IT DOWN TO

17:00.853 --> 17:02.488
ITS CUSTOMERS.

17:02.488 --> 17:04.991
>> Reporter: HECO HAS APPROVALS

17:04.991 --> 17:06.692
FOR ROOFTOP SOLAR MOVING AGAIN

17:06.692 --> 17:07.860
AND HOPES TO TRIPLE THE AMOUNT

17:07.860 --> 17:09.929
OF ROOFTOP SOLAR BY 2030, BUT IT

17:09.929 --> 17:10.930
MAY NOT BE IN A POSITION TO

17:10.930 --> 17:13.332
DECIDE.

17:13.332 --> 17:15.601
LAST DECEMBER, HECO ANNOUNCED IT

17:15.601 --> 17:17.069
WAS BEING SOLD TO NEXTERA, A

17:17.069 --> 17:19.805
FLORIDA-BASED UTILITY GIANT.

17:19.805 --> 17:20.806
IF THE DEAL WITH NEXTERA DOES GO

17:20.806 --> 17:22.241
THROUGH, HAWAII'S ELECTRICITY

17:22.241 --> 17:23.442
CONSUMERS WILL BE SERVICED BY A

17:23.442 --> 17:24.610
COMPANY THAT SAYS IT IS

17:24.610 --> 17:26.212
COMMITTED TO RENEWABLE ENERGY

17:26.212 --> 17:28.314
SOURCES-- AT THIS POINT,

17:28.314 --> 17:29.448
PRIMARILY UTILITY-SCALE SOLAR

17:29.448 --> 17:32.084
AND WIND INSTALLATIONS.

17:32.084 --> 17:34.387
THAT MEANS BIG SOLAR AND WIND

17:34.387 --> 17:35.888
FARMS, WHICH TODAY PRODUCE MORE

17:35.888 --> 17:37.323
RENEWABLE ENERGY ACROSS THE

17:37.323 --> 17:39.025
COUNTRY THAN THE SMALL-SCALE

17:39.025 --> 17:40.059
ROOFTOP SYSTEMS THAT ARE SO

17:40.059 --> 17:41.928
POPULAR ON HAWAII.

17:41.928 --> 17:43.829
IT'S STILL THE OLD MODEL,

17:43.829 --> 17:45.498
THOUGH-- A UTILITY PRODUCING ALL

17:45.498 --> 17:47.500
THE POWER, JUST USING A

17:47.500 --> 17:48.434
DIFFERENT SOURCE AND SELLING IT

17:48.434 --> 17:50.469
VIRTUALLY AS A MONOPOLY.

17:50.469 --> 17:52.004
THAT IS NOT THE HAWAII WAY, OR

17:52.004 --> 17:53.606
AT LEAST THE WAY MANY HERE HAVE

17:53.606 --> 17:55.408
SAID THEY INSIST ON GOING-- TO

17:55.408 --> 17:56.242
HAVE A CHOICE.

17:56.242 --> 17:58.644
>> ONCE WE GET THIS THING

17:58.644 --> 18:00.613
POWERED, A YEAR AND A HALF OF

18:00.613 --> 18:02.915
FRUSTRATION, WE'LL GET OVER IT.

18:02.915 --> 18:04.483
>> Reporter: FOR CARLTON HO AND

18:04.483 --> 18:06.052
HIS FAMILY, THAT DAY FINALLY

18:06.052 --> 18:07.787
ARRIVED AFTER A YEAR AND A HALF

18:07.787 --> 18:08.487
OF WAITING.

