>> Sreenivasan: AND NOW TO THE

18:28.374 --> 18:29.241
ARTS.

18:29.241 --> 18:30.977
MORE THAN 65 YEARS AGO, IN THE

18:30.977 --> 18:32.144
LATE 1940s, "LIFE" MAGAZINE

18:32.144 --> 18:33.779
ASSIGNED ACCLAIMED PHOTOGRAPHER

18:33.779 --> 18:35.281
GORDON PARKS TO SHOOT A PIECE

18:35.281 --> 18:36.315
DEPICTING LIFE FOR AFRICAN-

18:36.315 --> 18:38.117
AMERICANS UNDER SEGREGATION.

18:38.117 --> 18:39.819
HE CHOSE TO RETURN HOME AND

18:39.819 --> 18:40.653
PROFILE HIS FORMER CLASSMATES IN

18:40.653 --> 18:42.188
KANSAS.

18:42.188 --> 18:44.023
BUT THE SERIES WAS NEVER

18:44.023 --> 18:46.125
PUBLISHED AND THE PICTURES NEVER

18:46.125 --> 18:47.460
SAW THE LIGHT OF DAY, UNTIL NOW.

18:47.460 --> 18:48.461
JARED BOWEN OF WGBH HAS OUR

18:48.461 --> 18:49.962
STORY.

18:49.962 --> 18:51.597
>> Reporter: THIS WAS THE

18:51.597 --> 18:53.132
PICTURE THAT LAUNCHED THE MUSEUM

18:53.132 --> 18:55.768
OF FINE ARTS' KAREN HAAS ON A

18:55.768 --> 18:57.136
CURATORIAL QUEST TO LEARN WHAT

18:57.136 --> 18:58.637
BROUGHT PHOTOGRAPHER GORDON

18:58.637 --> 19:01.140
PARKS BACK TO FORT SCOTT,

19:01.140 --> 19:03.642
KANSAS, HIS HOMETOWN, IN 1950.

19:03.642 --> 19:06.445
WHAT SHE UNCOVERED WAS A TROVE,

19:06.445 --> 19:07.580
A COMPREHENSIVE LOOK AT BLACK

19:07.580 --> 19:09.749
LIFE UNDER SEGREGATION.

19:09.749 --> 19:11.951
>> HE HAD THE POWER TO GO BACK

19:11.951 --> 19:13.586
AND TELL THE STORIES OF AFRICAN

19:13.586 --> 19:15.254
AMERICAN FAMILIES-- FRIENDS OF

19:15.254 --> 19:17.590
HIS, PEOPLE WHO TRUSTED HIM, WHO

19:17.590 --> 19:19.692
LOOKED RIGHT INTO HIS CAMERA AND

19:19.692 --> 19:21.727
WHO REALLY BELIEVED THAT HE

19:21.727 --> 19:24.897
WOULD DO RIGHT BY THEM; THAT HE

19:24.897 --> 19:25.965
HAD THIS OPPORTUNITY TO SORT OF

19:25.965 --> 19:27.066
COUNTER ALL THE STEREOTYPES OF

19:27.066 --> 19:28.434
AFRICAN AMERICANS.

19:28.434 --> 19:30.202
>> Reporter: THIS EXHIBITION

19:30.202 --> 19:32.271
COMPRISES THE PHOTOGRAPHS PARKS

19:32.271 --> 19:33.873
TOOK ON ASSIGNMENT FOR "LIFE"

19:33.873 --> 19:34.874
MAGAZINE.

19:34.874 --> 19:36.575
HE HAD PITCHED THE STORY, TO

19:36.575 --> 19:38.277
RETURN HOME TO KANSAS FOR AN

19:38.277 --> 19:39.178
EXTREMELY PERSONAL TAKE ON

19:39.178 --> 19:41.347
SEGREGATION.

19:41.347 --> 19:43.783
>> HE DECIDES TO GO BACK AND

19:43.783 --> 19:45.918
SEEK OUT HIS CLASSMATES FROM

19:45.918 --> 19:48.020
ELEMENTARY SCHOOL-- AND IT TURNS

19:48.020 --> 19:49.889
OUT IT WAS THE ENTIRE CLASS OF

19:49.889 --> 19:52.558
1927 THAT HE WAS LOOKING FOR,

19:52.558 --> 19:55.661
ALL THE 11 CLASSMATES-- AND TO

19:55.661 --> 19:57.029
LOOK AT WHERE THEIR LIVES HAD

19:57.029 --> 19:59.598
GONE AND WHAT THEIR EXPERIENCES

19:59.598 --> 20:01.000
HAD BEEN IN THE 20-PLUS YEARS

20:01.000 --> 20:02.501
SINCE HE'D SEEN THEM.

20:02.501 --> 20:03.569
>> Reporter: IT WASN'T EASY FOR

20:03.569 --> 20:05.204
PARKS TO RETURN HOME.

20:05.204 --> 20:07.039
KANSAS AND FORT SCOTT HAD BEEN

20:07.039 --> 20:08.307
RIFE WITH RACISM THROUGHOUT HIS

20:08.307 --> 20:10.042
HARDSCRABBLE CHILDHOOD.

20:10.042 --> 20:10.709
>> HE WAS THE YOUNGEST OF 15

20:10.709 --> 20:13.245
CHILDREN.

20:13.245 --> 20:14.613
HIS FATHER WAS A TENANT FARMER,

20:14.613 --> 20:17.850
HIS MOTHER WAS A MAID.

20:17.850 --> 20:20.953
HE DESCRIBED HIS LIFE AS HAVING

20:20.953 --> 20:23.022
BEEN DISCRIMINATED AGAINST AND

20:23.022 --> 20:24.223
REALLY FELT THE NEED TO GET

20:24.223 --> 20:25.391
AWAY.

20:25.391 --> 20:26.559
>> Reporter: AS HE TRACKED DOWN

20:26.559 --> 20:28.961
HIS CLASSMATES SOME 20 YEARS

20:28.961 --> 20:30.496
AFTER HE'D LAST SEEN THEM, HE

20:30.496 --> 20:32.631
FOUND THAT NEARLY ALL HAD MOVED

20:32.631 --> 20:34.834
AWAY, SOME TO CHICAGO'S SOUTH

20:34.834 --> 20:35.601
SIDE.

20:35.601 --> 20:37.870
>> HE FOUND ONE FRIEND, MASEL,

20:37.870 --> 20:39.405
WHO WAS IN VERY DIRE STRAITS,

20:39.405 --> 20:40.306
AND HE DESCRIBED HER AS THE

20:40.306 --> 20:41.707
CLASS TRAGEDY.

20:41.707 --> 20:44.677
SHE WAS LIVING WITH AN ABUSIVE

20:44.677 --> 20:46.779
HUSBAND WHO ACTUALLY HELD UP

20:46.779 --> 20:48.114
GORDON PARKS WITH A GUN AND TOOK

20:48.114 --> 20:48.914
ALL HIS MONEY.

20:48.914 --> 20:49.915
>> Reporter: SHE WAS THE

20:49.915 --> 20:52.251
EXCEPTION.

20:52.251 --> 20:53.652
BY AND LARGE, PARKS FOUND HIS

20:53.652 --> 20:54.920
CLASSMATES, LIKE HIMSELF, HAD

20:54.920 --> 20:56.989
IMPROVED THEIR LIVES.

20:56.989 --> 20:58.390
>> ANOTHER ONE OF HIS CLASSMATE

20:58.390 --> 21:00.359
HAD FOUND A VERY BIG JOB AT

21:00.359 --> 21:02.628
CAMPBELL SOUP WHICH APPARENTLY

21:02.628 --> 21:04.263
WAS A FACTORY THAT HIRED A LOT

21:04.263 --> 21:06.298
OF AFRICAN AMERICAN WORKERS.

21:06.298 --> 21:08.934
SO, SOME PEOPLE WERE LIVING VERY

21:08.934 --> 21:10.903
MIDDLE-CLASS LIVES, BUT NEARLY

21:10.903 --> 21:12.404
ALL OF THE FAMILIES THAT HE MET

21:12.404 --> 21:13.672
WITH WERE LIVING IN MOSTLY

21:13.672 --> 21:15.141
AFRICAN AMERICAN NEIGHBORHOODS.

21:15.141 --> 21:17.076
>> Reporter: "LIFE" MAGAZINE

21:17.076 --> 21:19.111
NEVER PUBLISHED THE PARKS STORY.

21:19.111 --> 21:21.280
HAAS SPECULATES IT WAS BUMPED

21:21.280 --> 21:22.414
FOR BREAKING NEWS, AND, BY THE

21:22.414 --> 21:23.782
TIME IT COULD BE PUBLISHED, THE

21:23.782 --> 21:24.783
SUBJECTS' LIVES HAD ALREADY

21:24.783 --> 21:27.920
CHANGED DRAMATICALLY.

21:27.920 --> 21:30.556
SO, HERE, 65 YEARS LATER, PARKS'

21:30.556 --> 21:31.590
PERSPECTIVE FINALLY SEES THE

21:31.590 --> 21:33.526
LIGHT OF DAY.

21:33.526 --> 21:35.127
>> ONE VERY EXCITING THING IS

21:35.127 --> 21:37.429
THAT WE'VE RECENTLY REPRODUCED

