>> Sreenivasan: WHEN KEVIN CARR

22:23.108 --> 22:24.476
CROSSED THE FINISH LINE IN

22:24.476 --> 22:25.644
DEVON, ENGLAND, EARLIER THIS

22:25.644 --> 22:27.112
WEEK, HE COMPLETED A TEST OF

22:27.112 --> 22:28.480
ENDURANCE AND BROKE A RECORD FOR

22:28.480 --> 22:29.715
RUNNING AROUND THE WORLD IN THE

22:29.715 --> 22:31.483
FASTEST TIME.

22:31.483 --> 22:32.384
CARR TOOK ON THE CHALLENGE TO

22:32.384 --> 22:33.652
RAISE AWARENESS FOR MENTAL

22:33.652 --> 22:34.753
ILLNESS, SOMETHING HE SUFFERED

22:34.753 --> 22:36.088
FROM EARLIER IN HIS LIFE.

22:36.088 --> 22:38.357
I.T.N.'S RUPERT EVELYN REPORTS.

22:38.357 --> 22:40.359
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

22:40.359 --> 22:42.728
>> Reporter: FOR THE LAST 20

22:42.728 --> 22:43.662
MONTHS, KEVIN CARR HAS RUN MORE

22:43.662 --> 22:45.998
THAN A MARATHON A DAY.

22:45.998 --> 22:47.967
HAVING LEFT IN THE SUMMER OF

22:47.967 --> 22:49.568
2013, HE FINALLY COMPLETES WHAT

22:49.568 --> 22:50.603
IS BY ANY MEASURE AN EPIC

22:50.603 --> 22:55.441
JOURNEY.

22:55.441 --> 22:57.209
IT HAS BEEN BOTH A PHYSICAL AND

22:57.209 --> 22:58.911
MENTAL TEST OF ENDURANCE FOR A

22:58.911 --> 23:00.980
MAN WHO BY HIS OWN ADMISSION HAS

23:00.980 --> 23:02.648
HAD HIS OWN DEMONS TO OVERCOME.

23:02.648 --> 23:05.384
>> I JUST WANTED TO PROVE IF YOU

23:05.384 --> 23:06.986
HAVE BEEN MENTALLY ILL OR ARE

23:06.986 --> 23:08.621
SUFFERING AT THE MOMENT, THAT

23:08.621 --> 23:09.521
YOU SHOULDN'T LET ANYONE TELL

23:09.521 --> 23:10.823
YOU IT'S A WEAKNESS.

23:10.823 --> 23:11.924
I'VE LITERALLY JUST TAKEN ON THE

23:11.924 --> 23:12.491
WORLD.

23:12.491 --> 23:14.960
>> Reporter: MILLIONS OF STEPS,

23:14.960 --> 23:16.262
THOUSANDS OF MILES, AND THE

23:16.262 --> 23:17.496
WORLD RECORD FOR RUNNING AROUND

23:17.496 --> 23:18.631
THE WORLD.

23:18.631 --> 23:20.633
>> IT'S DEFINITELY

23:20.633 --> 23:21.867
UNCOMFORTABLE, YOU KNOW, NOT

23:21.867 --> 23:25.638
FUN.

23:25.638 --> 23:27.406
IT'S... AND FOR LONG STRETCHES.

23:27.406 --> 23:29.408
YOU MIGHT HAVE A BAD MONTH.

23:29.408 --> 23:31.010
>> Reporter: MOSTLY ALONE ON A

23:31.010 --> 23:32.478
GLOBAL ROAD, THE WORLD HAS

23:32.478 --> 23:35.014
THROWN EVERYTHING AT HIM--

23:35.014 --> 23:36.849
FROZEN IN NORWAY, BITTEN BY

23:36.849 --> 23:39.818
MOSQUITOES IN INDIA, AND DWARFED

23:39.818 --> 23:40.619
BY THE ANDES-- BUT IT WAS PEOPLE

23:40.619 --> 23:41.854
WHO WERE THE GREATEST THREAT.

